      • onCallExt

        void onCallExt​(MkvOnBehalfOfRegistrationResult res,
               String token,
               String customErrMsg)
        Event is generated when the Daemon replies to a request to any of the following methods for registering a virtual Platform Component on-behalf-of:
        • MkvPlatform.registerOnBehalfOf(String, String, String, String, MkvOnBehalfOfRegistrationListener)
        • MkvPlatform.registerOnBehalfOf(String, String, String, String, String, MkvOnBehalfOfRegistrationListener)
        • MkvPlatform.registerOnBehalfOf(String, String, String, String, String, String, String, String, MkvOnBehalfOfRegistrationListener)
        • MkvPlatform.registerOnBehalfOf(String, String, String, String, String, String, String, String, String, MkvOnBehalfOfRegistrationListener)
        This event includes an optional custom error message, in case of External Authentication response.
        Parameters:
        res - the result of the request, as processed by the Daemon
        token - the authentication token associated with the virtual Platform Component just registered in
        customErrMsg - the custom error message, if provided by the Daemon
